  2021,"10",/general-conference/2021/10/55douglas,Elder Sean Douglas,55,"Alma 32:16. The full verse reads, “Therefore, blessed are they whohumblethemselves without beingcompelledto be humble; or rather, in other words, blessed is he that believeth in the word of God, and is baptized withoutstubbornnessof heart, yea, without being brought to know the word, or even compelled to know, before they will believe” (emphasis added). Note that the Lord desires that we believe without being compelled to be humble, without being stubborn, without being “brought” to know, and without being compelled to “know” before we will believe."
